    <div class="about-path-inner">
      <div class="about-path-aside">
        <span class="about-path-aside-label">Background</span>
        <div class="about-path-year">—</div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-path-body">
        <p>My path wasn't linear. Early in life, I made choices that led to four years in a medium-security federal prison. That experience — inside institutions that affect real people — shaped a commitment to accuracy, restraint, fairness, and careful reporting about systems where stakes are highest and second chances are rarely guaranteed.</p>
        <div class="about-path-pull">
          <p>"Not applause, but alignment. Not noise, but impact. Not reputation, but responsibility."</p>
        </div>
        <p>That season became a turning point. I learned the cost of wasted potential and the meaning of second chances. I have been building from that understanding ever since — first in technology, and now in journalism that tries to hold institutions to the same standard of honesty I learned the hard way.</p>
